manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Assured Quality, Fast Speed, High Performance This Timetec memory is designed to help your desktop system run faster and smoother, it is one of the easiest and most affordable ways to improve your desktop’s performance. It allows your desktop system to load programs faster, increase responsiveness and run data-intensive programs with ease.
Specifications Module Type DDR3 Non-ECC Unbuffered UDIMM Frequency 1600MHz CAS Latency CL11 Capacity 4GB / 8GB Voltage 1.35V / 1.5V Pins 240 Pin Demensions 30(H) x 133.4(L)mm
Increase Multitasking Timetec memory is engineered to maximize effectiveness and efficiency of your desktop system and increase your desktop’s multitasking capabilities.
Extensive Compatible All Timtec modules are extensively working at the component level for voltage and temperature resistances, signal integrity and software compatibility to ensure high stability.

High-quality Components and Strict Tests Timetec has selected a high-quality IC die that has undergone comprehensive compatibility and reliability testing to ensure the memory that delivers both stability and compatibility.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 5.0 out of 5 stars Value priced, meets or exceeds description, works as advertised and is a value.
reviews.reviewText: I purchase several things on Amazon and was giving pretty in-depth reviews. From this point on, here's the new agenda…. if it works as advertised, is well made, meets or exceeds the description, is a value, and arrives in a fair amount of time, it will get a "star rating" equal to what my expectations were/are. If it doesn't meet these criteria, then I will most definitely and descriptively tell the short comings of the products and you as a consumer will not have to go through the trouble of buying the product without some background knowledge. If the sell pulls that item and relists under another description, I will put the exact same review on the seller's feedback page. Sellers have done this a couple of times in the past, and I was true to my word then as well as now. DR

reviews.reviewText: Perfect and exact for my older tower server PC It was exact specs for this Dell OptiPlex and it made a night and day performance boost it needed!This ram doubled the available memory, and opened up 2 slots for future ram, if we decide to keep this pc, so it was a no brainer, Plug and play, up and running and I have stressed this server and the new ram to the extreme and it has not had a single issue,,The pc is used in archiving a retail store with a dozen other machines all networked to this machine, heavy demands and peak hours dried up the previous available ram from day to day business and this Ram installed, no more freezing, delays or locking up.The ram expansion has bought us time as a non profit to seek time to secure funds to replace everything in the future,, hopefully with the next fiscal budget.I would recommend this ram as an option to keep the older functional pc's running and less electronics in the recycle bins,

I recently upgraded my Dell OptiPlex 3020 with the Timetec 16GB KIT (2x8GB) DDR3L / DDR3 1600MHz PC3L-12800 RAM, and the improvement in performance is truly remarkable. The installation was incredibly smooth and straightforward, with no need for any firmware updates.This RAM kit has significantly boosted the speed and responsiveness of my computer. Multitasking is now a breeze, with no lag or slowdown, even when running multiple applications simultaneously. The increase in memory has also positively impacted the overall efficiency of the system, allowing for smoother operation and faster processing times.The compatibility of the Timetec RAM with my older Dell OptiPlex 3020 was flawless. It seamlessly integrated into my existing setup, providing an instant upgrade to my PC's performance. The value for money is excellent, considering the significant boost in speed and multitasking capabilities.For anyone looking to upgrade their older PC's performance without breaking the bank, I highly recommend the Timetec 16GB KIT. It's an affordable yet highly effective way to extend the life and usability of your computer. This upgrade has revitalized my Dell OptiPlex 3020, making it feel like a much newer machine.
